---
// src/components/SocialScraping.astro
---
<section class="py-16 bg-white">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8 text-center shadow-sm">
      <div class="flex justify-center mb-4">
        <!-- A simple code icon to visually represent the 'meta' aspect -->
        <svg class="h-8 w-8 text-gray-400" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M17.25 6.75 22.5 12l-5.25 5.25m-10.5 0L1.5 12l5.25-5.25m7.5-3-4.5 12" />
        </svg>
      </div>
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">Behind the Data</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        The "Valued Colleagues & Thinkers" section above is generated by a custom Python script. This tool uses the <strong class="font-semibold text-gray-700">Selenium</strong> library to automate a browser, analyze my recent professional engagement on LinkedIn, and compile a ranked list of the individuals and organizations I interact with most. It's a small example of building a fit-for-purpose data pipeline.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>